    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Mongo3 - Awesome admin interface]]></title>
    <link href="http://mytrile.github.com/blog/2010/02/22/mongo3-awesome-admin-interface/"/>
    <updated>2010-02-22T00:00:00+02:00</updated>
    <id>http://mytrile.github.com/blog/2010/02/22/mongo3-awesome-admin-interface</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>MongoDB is great implementation of NoSQL idea. But right now it's lacking admin interface except the javascript based console. <a href="http://github.com/derailed/mongo3">Mongo3</a> is here for the rescue:</p>


<p>&#13;</p>

<p><img src="http://media.tumblr.com/tumblr_l8oayf2X6d1qcx25j.png" /></p>


<p>&#13;</p>

<p>As you can see Mongo3 allows you to manage your mongoDB clusters using a web based admin console. It's written in Ruby using Sinatra.</p>


<p>&#13;</p>

<p>Running Mongo3 in 3 steps:</p>


<p>&#13;</p>

<ol><li>Get the gem <code>sudo gem install mongo3</code></li>&#13;
<li>Create .mongo3 file in your home dir with config details<br /><script src="http://gist.github.com/310914.js"></script></li>&#13;
<li>Fire it up <code>mongo3</code></li>&#13;
</ol>


<p>PS: Another project to look is <a href="http://github.com/ahe/mongo_admin">mongo_admin</a></p>


<p></p>
]]></content>
